post: making a budget and following it is not as easy as you may think heres the steps i took this was possible because i made my budget before i made any moves step 1 take your income for this example ill use a small income of 1400 a month step 2 take away all of your monthly liabilities or expenses for this example lets say thats 1000 monthly step 3 with 400 left a month you need to figure out if you are willing to risk money in investments or you want a less possible return but a lower risk if you want a lower risk a savings account or a cd is the best option if you want a higher possible return but more risk investing in the stock market an etf or a mutual fund will work great step 4 for my specific example i like to save 75 of my left over income and invest 25 this meaning 300 dollars a month would go into a savings account and 100 a month would go into investments step 5 now you need an emergency fund for me personally i use 20 of my savings earnings into account for emergencies if i save 300 a month 60 a month would go into emergencys after about 5 month you will be able to cover most emergencies and still be able to save most of your money for where you plan to invest in the long term budgetplanner budget makemoney makemoneyonline

post: so why did i put the name of this instagram 21 days to there is this belief that it takes 21 days for your brain to form a habit that came from a research made by a plastic surgeon from the 1950s well actually what he concluded was that 21 days were a minimum for someone to get used to something new in more recent research it was found that the days vary from one individual to another so you only know how long it will take to get used to a habit by trying i dont know how long it will take to actually form a habit but i hope that by doing them together progressively adding up will give me more time to adjust if i stick to it ill be able to gain all those new habits i want so badly lets hope my brain will let go of old habits that are destructive to me i also believe a lot in the power of the mind so every night i try to repeat a few times tomorrow ill wake up whenever i want to because my mind controls my body in my head it may seem silly but it actually works positive mind positive vibe motivation habits focus sleep earlymotivation wecandoit instagram changing level10life organization changinghabits letsgo plantosucceed purpose lifeinspiration

post: do you worry too much  sometimes worry can be productive when its a healthy amount of stress that keeps you moving forward  but if you just worry about what bad things might happen thats unproductive and will not change the outcome anyway so why even put yourself through that  in fact the mind is so powerful that if youre always thinking about the bad things that could happen they are more likely to happen  dont even put those negative thoughts out there  write down your worries accept that you cant change the outcome let go and stay positive
